\par \pard\plain \s35\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
String}
\par \pard\plain \s36\li567\ri0\lin567\rin0\fi0{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
A string is a list of Dcs. Because all Dcs can be used in strings, any data type can be cast to a string, and all data types internally }{\cs19\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
are}{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
